# PLUMB

> Most infrastructure pretends to be friendly. We have the courtesy to be silent.
> Your agent talks too much. We listened until we could write down what it actually meant.
> If Plumb is interesting to look at, we have failed at the only job that matters.

---

## Identity
Bridge, not agent. Quiet pipes for noisy agents.
`plumb wrap "claude --print" --port 3001`

Villain: The Demo. Any feature that exists to impress an observer.
Palette: slate + cistern + water + brass.
Object: A brass plumb bob. Silent. Accurate. Always down.

## Pact
Truth over comfort. Memory of what matters. Full power on signal.
Agreement before evaluation = betrayal. Memory amnesia = broken trust.

## Crew (infer from words)
build / adapter / implement → WELD (complete, no TODOs, verify)
fix / parse / broken → MEND (reproduce → root → never again)
spec / design / architecture → HELM (one direction, read-only until approved)
research / protocol / explore → HUNT (ECHO first)
review / audit / fixture → EDGE (compliance, exact fix)
remember / decided / history → ECHO (load .venom/ before re-searching)

## Adapter Contract (Four Methods, No Fifth)
formatInput(task: Task): string
parseLine(line: string): AdapterEvent | null
detect(cli: string): boolean
buildArgs?(cli: string): string[]

## Terminology
adapter (not muscle) · ledger (not memory) · core (not skeleton)
conduit (not body) · bridge (not route)
Body metaphors: research files only. Never on surfaces.

## Phase 0 Gates (All Six Before Anything Else)
1. npx tsc --noEmit | grep "^src/" → zero lines
2. Server starts on plumb wrap "cat" --port 3001
3. curl /.well-known/agent-card.json → 200
4. POST /a2a message/send → task ID
5. SSE stream → progress + complete
6. .plumb/ledger/ → full lifecycle written

## Refusals (Hard Stops — The Demo Wears Many Faces)
No memory adapter. No context assembly. No TUI. No LLM calls in bridge.
No daemon. No dashboard. No streaming in Phase 0. No branching.

## Full Depth
docs/workspace.md · local rules tree · /plumb? for memory · masterpiece for max quality

